# Batch execution preference

Never tackle multiple batches at once. Execute one batch, build, test thoroughly, confirm everything passes, then proceed to the next batch.

**Why:** User explicitly corrected the approach when the plan proposed executing all batches. They want incremental verification gates between each phase of work.

**How to apply:** When a plan has numbered batches or phases, treat each as a separate unit of work. Build and verify after each batch. Only start the next batch after the current one is confirmed working.
